<title type="html"><![CDATA[On Cartridge Sound Mixing]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=137&amp;p=859#p859"><![CDATA[
ALL Famicom carts use the pass-through method (Famicom audio comes in on pin 45, mapper sound gets mixed in, then the result goes out pin 46) - cartridges which do not use expansion audio simply short pins 45 and 46 together.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Thu Jan 06, 2005 12:00 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
